  4x Bill Ferny<br>
 <br>
  4x <a href="javascript:card_browser(135)">Desperate Defense of the Ring</a><br>
  2x <a href="javascript:card_browser(163)">Thin and Stretched</a><br>
  4x <a href="javascript:card_browser(867)">Enduring Evil</a> <br>
  4x <a href="javascript:card_browser(140)">Hate</a><br>
  1x <a href="javascript:card_browser(142)">The Irresistible Shadow</a><br>
  1x Verily I Come<br>
36 Total    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck has gone through many changes and modifications, the one thing that has never changed is SUPER BILL. What you may ask is that? Well the key to the deck is the Bill Ferny&#39;s and the Desperate Defense of the Ring cards.<br>
<br>
Play your trackers to remove the roaming, use the Tower Assassin to kill Ally&#39;s, play the Morgul hunter to slow them down.<br>
<br>
The big Kick on how it Really works: <br>
Drop 3 or 4 Desperate defences on a SINGLE companion, then PLAY A BILL FENRY (I play 4 AND a Skulker cycles him back into your deck). The Desperate defense says &#39;when the companion is assigned...&#39; not &#39;when you assign this minion...&#39; Lets see that would be 4 burdens or 12 cards please. If you get your Desperate Defenses on early and a random Thin and Streached for another Burden or so, Bam! Enduring Evil squishes you like a bug (oh yeah, its really funny when you can spot hobbits other than Frodo, 2 Orc assassins and 2 hobbits without weapons = overwelmed hobbits, if you have to fight Frodo an Enduring Evil its just icing on the cake). You may be tempted for a few Under the Watching Eye&#39;s  (there are 10 trackers) but don&#39;t be fooled you need the exertions for your Hates, Desperate Defenses and the random Thin and Stretched. You may also ask why no Bowmen? The answer is simple, you won&#39;t be getting that much twilight to play around with. Point: it will take you a MINIMUM 4 shadow from sites 1-6 just to drop a single DD, you don&#39;t have the pool for the Bowman, you won&#39;t need them. You say wait you have 4 Hates... WHY? well a random Sam HURTS this deck, I HATE SAM, Sam is now DEAD. <br>
<br>
The Free peoples side is pretty straight forward, whatever can&#39;t be shot dead will face a HUGE Gondor Man, and DIE, or deal 1 wound. I love the swanship card if I ever need an extra archery ocloberon to throw in front of some big baddie the allies are sacrificial. Frodo 98% of the time will not have to fight, therefore no wasted card slots for him. Sting is good to keep the twilight pool down, also you usually only move 1 site a turn (it will give you time to set up the kill) the Sting will let you see what you have to deal with later. The mirror is not needed, I think its fun to burn their hand. Sting, OHHH he has that! Mirror, Mirror ;)<br>
<br>
If you wanted to modify this deck for a Dual way to win you could remove the Tower Assassins and Morgul Hunters and even a tracker or two to add in a couple of thoes Tower Lieutenants and a few more discard random cards cards to win by spoting 5 burdens and a decked apponent.<br>
